RACE.FOOTNOTES: ACCEL ROSE got bumped at the start by GERMANY JAYVO breaking outwards, raced five paths off the inside down the backstretch before tucking briefly three wide at the nine-sixteenths and then to the two path through the turn, came under coaxing at the three-eighths, swung three wide into upper stretch and was leaned on and carried in to the two path before getting bumped at the three-sixteenths by HERECOMES SCARLETT, dug in under a drive between foes steadily gaining to the finish to be up in the final jumps to the wire. BALENTINA dueled from the two path with GEORGIE'S LADIES to her outside, tucked inside through the turn coming under coaxing near the quarter pole, spun just off the inside for home and took to the inside briefly straightened away, dug in under threat from a pair and clung to command until collared in the final strides to the finish. HERECOMES SCARLETT four then three wide in pursuit, came under coaxing at the three-eighths, swung four then three wide into upper stretch straightened away leaning on ACCEL ROSE and bumping that rival to the two path at the three-sixteenths, dug in under a drive outside a pair through the final furlong before ultimately being repelled in the late stages while clear for the show honors. WELCOMETOMYWORLD stumbled at the start recovering outwards and bumping GERMANY JAYVO against ACCEL ROSE, chased along the inside under a ride from the three-eighths, angled out five wide into upper stretch and offered up a mild bid. GERMANY JAYVO broke out at the start bumping with ACCEL ROSE then got bumped by WELCOMETOMYWORLD, who recovered outwards from a stumble, chased just off the inside, angled four wide into upper stretch, made no impact. GEORGIE'S LADIES dueled three then two wide with BALENTINA to her inside, came under coaxing three furlongs from home, spun just off the inside into upper stretch shaken off and folded. AKIVA hard to load prior to the start, chased five then four wide under coaxing from the three-eighths, swung three to four wide into upper stretch, tired and was eased to the finish.

INTO TOURING came out at the start and bumped lightly with a foe, settled on the inside, was roused on the far turn, moved to the two path late on that bend, gained four wide into the stretch, held a reasonable striking position under a drive into the final furlong but lacked the needed response and came up empty. IRONY bumped lightly with an opponent at the start, rounded the first turn in the two path, settled towards the rear, was roused while three then four wide on the far turn, came six wide into the stretch and failed to respond. HEARTBURN was forced out at the start, traveled four wide around the opening bend, settled on the outside, angled in inside the five-eighths pole, saved ground while given her cue on the far turn, turned into the stretch in the two path then bumped with the winner and came up empty. RACE.FOOTNOTES: QUEENS OVER THREES steadied at the start in behind GOTHAM GRAY who broke inwards taking over her lane, chased along the inside from mid pack, continued just off the inside into upper stretch set down for the drive, tipped out straightened away, dug in under a drive rallying to issue a challenge inside the final furlong and was just up over a pair of rivals on the wire. GOTHAM GRAY broke in at the start forcing QUEENS OVER THREES to steady off her heels, raced three wide in closest aim of the leader coming under coaxing near the quarter pole, continued three wide into upper stretch and then took to the two path straightened away, dug in under a drive steadily gaining on the leader, was just in the midst of taking command steps from the finish when nosed out herself and just missed on the line. DANCE WITH ME BABE showed the way in hand just off the inside, got set down taking the inside route into upper stretch, dug in under threat clinging stubbornly to command, then got nailed in the final jumps by a pair of foes and was forced to settle for the show honors. PAUCILOQUENT chased along the inside under coaxing from the five-sixteenths, angled three wide into upper stretch, closed well to the finish. GIGGLING GHOST chased along the inside under a ride from the five-sixteenths, cut the corner into upper stretch, ran on through to the wire. APRIL FIRST five paths off the inside down the backstretch, tucked to the two path through the turn coming under coaxing at the five-sixteenths, cut the corner into upper stretch and kicked on belatedly to the end. PUREST PERFORMANCE struck the off side stall at the start, chased just off the inside under coaxing from the five-sixteenths, spun three wide for home and was outfinished in the late stages. MY CARA MIA MINE chased just off the inside until tucked inside through the turn, came under coaxing at the five-sixteenths, angled out seven wide into upper stretch and made no impact. DREAMING OF CARLI got bumped at the start by GRACEFULNESS, who broke inwards, chased three then two wide, got let out swinging five wide into upper stretch and was unable to make an impact. MARY KATHERINE three to four wide in pursuit, came under coaxing at the five-sixteenths, angled six wide into upper stretch, offered no response. MIZZ ME four wide in pursuit, came under coaxing at the three-eighths, swung four to five wide into upper stretch and weakened. GRACEFULNESS broke in at the start bumping DREAMING OF CARLI, chased five wide under coaxing from the five-sixteenths, went seven wide into upper stretch and never threatened.
